<paragraph blockId="1.[148,978,497,1156]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[172,402,497,518]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Nomenclatural Status.</emphasis>
Available but invalid name, junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="LePeletier and Serville, 1828" authorityName="LePeletier and Serville" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Gnorimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[882,977,497,518]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Gnorimus</emphasis>
LePeletier and Serville, 1828
</taxonomicName>
as a reversal of precedence under Article 23.9.2 of the Code. This action was taken by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dechambre" box="[497,683,550,571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="229 - 232" refId="ref2887" refString="Dechambre, R. - P. 2001. Du bon usage du principe de priorite ou pourquoi Gnorimus doit rester Gnorimus (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae, Trichiinae). L'Entomologiste 57 (6): 229 - 232." type="journal article" year="2001">Dechambre (2001)</bibRefCitation>
to counteract the erroneous resurrection of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Stephens" authorityYear="1839" box="[301,426,577,598]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Aleurostictus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[301,426,577,598]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Aleurostictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid name by 
<bibRefCitation author="Adam" box="[643,775,572,598]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="5 - 17" refId="ref2663" refString="Adam, L. 1994. A check-list of the Hungarian Scarabaeoidea with the description of ten new taxa (Coleoptera). Folia Entomologica Hungarica 55: 5 - 17." type="journal article" year="1994">Ádám (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Tauzin" box="[831,974,577,598]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="231 - 281" refId="ref4160" refString="Tauzin, P. 2000. Le genre Aleurostictus Kirby, 1827: Contribution a sa connaissance et precision sur la distribution des especes (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae, Trichiinae, Trichiini). L'Entomologiste 56: 231 - 281." type="journal article" year="2000">Tauzin (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dechambre" box="[148,329,604,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="229 - 232" refId="ref2887" refString="Dechambre, R. - P. 2001. Du bon usage du principe de priorite ou pourquoi Gnorimus doit rester Gnorimus (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae, Trichiinae). L'Entomologiste 57 (6): 229 - 232." type="journal article" year="2001">Dechambre (2001)</bibRefCitation>
outlined the case against using 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Stephens" authorityYear="1839" box="[648,773,604,625]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Aleurostictus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[648,773,604,625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Aleurostictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by pointing out that 
<bibRefCitation author="Tauzin" box="[148,288,630,651]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="231 - 281" refId="ref4160" refString="Tauzin, P. 2000. Le genre Aleurostictus Kirby, 1827: Contribution a sa connaissance et precision sur la distribution des especes (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae, Trichiinae, Trichiini). L'Entomologiste 56: 231 - 281." type="journal article" year="2000">Tauzin (2000)</bibRefCitation>
violated Article 23.11 of the Code, which states that ‘‘If an author wishes to replace a name in prevailing usage by its older synonym when the conditions of Article 23.9.1 are met, he or she must apply to the Commission for a ruling under the plenary power.’’ No such application to the commission has been published in the 
<emphasis box="[148,508,736,757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature.</emphasis>
Additionally, the use of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Stephens" authorityYear="1839" box="[751,876,736,757]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Aleurostictus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[751,876,736,757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Aleurostictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid name by 
<bibRefCitation author="Adam" box="[237,366,758,784]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="5 - 17" refId="ref2663" refString="Adam, L. 1994. A check-list of the Hungarian Scarabaeoidea with the description of ten new taxa (Coleoptera). Folia Entomologica Hungarica 55: 5 - 17." type="journal article" year="1994">Ádám (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Tauzin" box="[414,551,763,784]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="231 - 281" refId="ref4160" refString="Tauzin, P. 2000. Le genre Aleurostictus Kirby, 1827: Contribution a sa connaissance et precision sur la distribution des especes (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae, Trichiinae, Trichiini). L'Entomologiste 56: 231 - 281." type="journal article" year="2000">Tauzin (2000)</bibRefCitation>
(and subsequent authors such as 
<bibRefCitation author="Whitehead" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref4307" refString="Whitehead, P. F. 2003. The noble chafer Aleurostictus nobilis (L., 1758) (Col., Scarabaeidae) in Britain. Proceedings of the Second Pan-European Conference on Saproxylic Beetles 6: 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="2003">Whitehead [2003]</bibRefCitation>
) all violate Article 23.9.6 which states ‘‘The deliberate use of a name contrary to Article 23.9.1, or the mentioning of a name in a synonymy, or its mere listing in an abstracting publication, or in a nomenclator or other index or list of names must not be taken into account in determining usage under Articles 23.9.1.1 and 23.9.1.2.’’ 
<bibRefCitation author="Tauzin" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="231 - 281" refId="ref4160" refString="Tauzin, P. 2000. Le genre Aleurostictus Kirby, 1827: Contribution a sa connaissance et precision sur la distribution des especes (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae, Trichiinae, Trichiini). L'Entomologiste 56: 231 - 281." type="journal article" year="2000">Tauzin (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Whitehead" box="[223,396,896,917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref4307" refString="Whitehead, P. F. 2003. The noble chafer Aleurostictus nobilis (L., 1758) (Col., Scarabaeidae) in Britain. Proceedings of the Second Pan-European Conference on Saproxylic Beetles 6: 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="2003">Whitehead (2003)</bibRefCitation>
, and perhaps others used 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Stephens" authorityYear="1839" box="[638,763,896,917]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Aleurostictus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[638,763,896,917]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Aleurostictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
incorrectly because of the ‘‘deliberate use of a name contrary to Article 23.9.1.’’ The use of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Stephens" authorityYear="1839" box="[821,946,922,943]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Aleurostictus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[821,946,922,943]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Aleurostictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Adam" box="[148,281,944,970]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="5 - 17" refId="ref2663" refString="Adam, L. 1994. A check-list of the Hungarian Scarabaeoidea with the description of ten new taxa (Coleoptera). Folia Entomologica Hungarica 55: 5 - 17." type="journal article" year="1994">Ádám (1994)</bibRefCitation>
is not to be considered for prevailing usage because it is listed in a checklist, which is a ‘‘mere listing in an... index or list of names.’’ The nomenclatural action of 
<bibRefCitation author="Dechambre" box="[383,563,1002,1023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="229 - 232" refId="ref2887" refString="Dechambre, R. - P. 2001. Du bon usage du principe de priorite ou pourquoi Gnorimus doit rester Gnorimus (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae, Trichiinae). L'Entomologiste 57 (6): 229 - 232." type="journal article" year="2001">Dechambre (2001)</bibRefCitation>
permanently gives 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LePeletier and Serville" authorityYear="1828" box="[754,849,1002,1023]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Gnorimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[754,849,1002,1023]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Gnorimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
priority over 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Stephens" authorityYear="1839" box="[148,273,1029,1050]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Aleurostictus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[148,273,1029,1050]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Aleurostictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
thus ending the debate over which name is valid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="286" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph blockId="1.[148,978,497,1156]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[172,314,1055,1076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">
<typeStatus box="[172,224,1055,1076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Type</typeStatus>
Species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[326,673,1055,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scarabaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilis">
<emphasis box="[326,511,1055,1076]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Scarabaeus nobilis</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 1758
</taxonomicName>
(now 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[742,912,1055,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Gnorimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilis">
<emphasis box="[742,912,1055,1076]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Gnorimus nobilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), here designated. 
<bibRefCitation author="Tauzin" box="[265,404,1082,1103]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" pagination="231 - 281" refId="ref4160" refString="Tauzin, P. 2000. Le genre Aleurostictus Kirby, 1827: Contribution a sa connaissance et precision sur la distribution des especes (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae, Trichiinae, Trichiini). L'Entomologiste 56: 231 - 281." type="journal article" year="2000">Tauzin (2000)</bibRefCitation>
erroneously listed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[595,780,1082,1103]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scarabaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilis">
<emphasis box="[595,780,1082,1103]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">Scarabaeus nobilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[858,899,1082,1103]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">type</typeStatus>
species ‘‘according to the original description.’’ However, two species were explicitly listed in the genus with the original description so one is selected here as the 
<typeStatus box="[821,862,1135,1156]" pageId="1" pageNumber="286">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
